		<category>
			<pattern>led bulbs</pattern>
			<template>
				LED bulbs can last for around 25,000 hours, whereas fluorescent bulbs can only last 8000 hours,
				and incandescent bulbs around 1000 hours.
				The upfront cost to buy an LED bulb is more than other types of bulbs, however they make up for it in the amount of energy they save.
				The price of running a 60-Watt incandescent bulb for 20 years (6 hours per day) is around £290. An equivalent LED bulb for the same amount of time would only cost £59!
